```python
import pandas as pd

# Sample DataFrame
data = {
    'group': ['A', 'A', 'B', 'B', 'C'],
    'value': [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Group by 'group' and calculate the sum of 'value' for each group
grouped_sum = df.groupby('group')['value'].sum().reset_index()

# Rename the 'value' column to 'sum_value'
grouped_sum.rename(columns={'value': 'sum_value'}, inplace=True)

# Merge the sum back to the original DataFrame
df = df.merge(grouped_sum, on='group', how='left')

print(df)
```
